            "answer_text": "Well, it\u2019s like you didn\u2019t even google the exact phrase! Mathematical Methods for Physics and Engineering by Riley, Hobson & Bence I mean, the phrasing is almost exactly what you\u2019ve already typed\u2026. Ether way, RileyHobsonBence is pretty much the bible of first year physics at Oxford, and the math in it takes you all the way up to the middle of third year (so I am told). It is packed full of questions to do and whilst I dislike some of the ways it treats linear algebra (there is a much simpler way to do some of it), it is a very good book. ",
